            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I am a happy parent for G.D.Goenka Global School.\nMy boy is in nursery standard. He was so much impacted upon during covid that adapting to new school environment was a challenge to him.\nThe school admission coordinator meenakshi mam, the pyp coordinator mandeep mam, principal mam were all so much cooperative in handling in his non adaptive phase of schooling.. that they listened, understood and catered to the required needs of the child..\nHis prenursery and nursery teachers were all very nice and gentle to kids.. the class teacher to student ratio is also very good which is approx. 2:15. Which is very rare to find..\nIn the class also, we had shadow teacher with him who was taking his special care.. that also benefitted him in several ways in his adapting to classroom environment, involving in various activities like plays, dance, physical education etc. And various other aspects like speaking in english, writing practice, colouring practice etc. And lastly making freinds in class, becoming socially amicable..\nAnd the class teacher assistance the didis in the class are so cooperative, humble and kind and gentle..  that they treat every child with special love and care..\nHe remembers all his teachers and didi when school breaks comes… reaches inside meenakshi mam's cabin to talk to her anytime..\n\nI would highly recommend the school to all of you..!!",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
